title: SpaceChain pivots to combine AI with Earth imagery
summary: The Singapore startup known for sending blockchain nodes into space is rolling out a service that integrates artificial intelligence with Earth imagery.

title: Psyche asteroid mission set for October launch
summary: A NASA mission to a large metallic asteroid is on track to launch in October after more than a year of delays, but the mission faces a potential challenge to those plans beyond the agency’s control.

title: L3Harris Selects Firefly To Launch US National Security Satellites
summary: Firefly Aerospace has signed an agreement with L3Harris Technologies to conduct three dedicated missions on Firefly's Alpha rocket. The satellites are currently being designed and constructed by L3Harris, under a $225 million contract awarded by the U.S. government.

title: Galactic Energy's Ceres-1 Reaches Orbit On First Sea Launch Mission
summary: China's Galactic Energy has successfully conducted their first sea launch, marking the company's ninth consecutive successful launch.

title: Ariane 6 One Step Closer, But Still No Launch Date
summary: Europe’s new Ariane 6 rocket is one step closer to launch today following a successful, if brief, engine test. A longer test is scheduled next month. Only then will European […]

title: Pentagon’s new plan to counter China includes swarms of smart satellites
summary: Under a new strategy to counter China’s military buildup, the Pentagon is advocating the use of low-cost autonomous platforms that can be mass produced and deployed at sea, on land, in the air and in space.

title: SDA Seeks Bids For 54 Hypersonic Missile-Tracking Satellites
summary: The Space Development Agency (SDA) has release a solicitation for the procurement of 54 satellites equipped with advanced infrared sensors.

title: US Space Force Unveils New Mission Statement
summary: The US Space Force in an effort to provide a clearer and more concise understanding of its mission has unveiled a new mission statement today. "Secure our nation's interests in, from, and to space"

title: NASA's Oxygen-Generating Experiment MOXIE Completes Mars Mission
summary: Riding with the Perseverance rover, the instrument has proved to be a viable technology for astronauts on Mars to produce oxygen for fuel and breathing.

title: MAG Aerospace and SAS partner for Space Force data-analytics contract
summary: MAG Aerospace is partnering with artificial intelligence specialist SAS to compete for U.S. Space Force data analytics contracts, the companies announced Sept. 6
